quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  22,39,Leave is given to those who fight because they were wronged -- surely God is able to help them
  22,40,"who were expelled from their habitations without right, except that they say 'Our Lord is God.' Had God not driven back the people, some by the means of others, there had been destroyed cloisters and churches, oratories and mosques, wherein God's Name is much mentioned. Assuredly God will help him who helps Him -- surely God is All-strong, All-mighty"
  22,41,"who, if We establish them in the land, perform the prayer, and pay the alms, and bid to honour, and forbid dishonour; and unto God belongs the issue of all affairs"
  22,42,"If they cry lies to thee, so too before them the people of Noah cried lies, and Ad and Thamood"
  22,43,"and the people of Abraham, the people of Lot"
  22,44,"and the men of Midian; to Moses also they cried lies. And I respited the unbelievers, then I seized them; and how was My horror"
  22,45,"How many a city We have destroyed in its evildoing, and now it is fallen down upon its turrets! How many a ruined well, a tall palace"
  22,46,"What, have they not journeyed in the land so that they have hearts to understand with or ears to hear with? It is not the eyes that are blind, but blind are the hearts within the breasts"